Site_Access_Procedure:
Request Temporary Access
To request temporary site access create a task and assign it to the ENS oncall. Include the following information:

Full Name:
Email:
Phone:
Govt ID#:
FB Facility Name:
Date(s) and Time of Access:
Short SOW:

Requests without an end date will not be processed.

Site Instructions
To enter our cage you must check in with security on the fifth floor. When you leave the elevator, the security office will be on your left. Present your govt issued photo ID and check out the appropriate badge. You will also need the corresponding pin number to access the cage.

Vendor Badges
Badge: 1804 Pin: 5499

If for some reason you need badges to more than one floor, four and seven for example, you will need two forms of ID.

Directions to Cage: Take the elevator to the 7th floor. Turn left out of the elevator and go through the man trap. First small staircase on the left has a palm scan, once the palm scan is successful, open the door up the small flight of stairs. The first cage nearest to the door is FB cage.

Grant Temporary Access
To grant temporary access use the Equinix portal to generate an access ticket. Provide the ticket number to access requester prior to visit date.

For further details visit the POP Access Wiki https://fburl.com/popaccess.
